description.plain:
Nessa Barrett (born August 6, 2002) moved from New Jersey to Los Angeles in pursuit of who she always wanted to be, but never believed she could become. That is, until she arrived at the recording studio for the first time in May 2020, sat down at the piano, and walked out with her first song, “Pain,” a soft-but-strong pop ballad that also served as her reintroduction to the world—it was released by Warner Records as her debut single just two months later. When Barrett began writing, she discovered that even when her songs focus on difficult emotions, the act of creating them was freeing. After a lifetime of holding back—facing down bullies, struggling with mental health, and wrestling with her dreams—she realized that music was the thing that made her feel right.

About a year before, Barrett began her search in a different medium and wound up with 16.3 million social media followers who’d only gotten a surface-level look at the 18-year-old. There, she adopted a bubbly façade, but as an artist she flourishes as herself: a bit of a tomboy who prefers oversized clothes, dabbles across genres, and feels comfortable voicing darker truths. “Pain” is the start of her story and was left musically bare to give Barrett room to evolve in any direction her experiences and emotions dictate. In addition to sharing cathartic songs—like her 808-boosted romantic-revenge anthem “if u love me”—she plans to use her platform for mental health advocacy, and to remind others who’ve struggled that they’re never alone.

songs.title: ​la di die

description.plain:
Marking her first release of 2021 and her first feature ever, Nessa Barrett finally releases the long-awaited grunge rock collaboration with jxdn on February, 19th.

The song had been teased several months before the release on both Nessa and jxdn’s TikTok accounts (@nessaabarrett and @jadenhossler, respectively).

songs.title: Pain

description.plain:
Nessa started paving her path to fame when she was inspired by her younger sister to download the video sharing platform known as TikTok.  As of August 14, 2020, she has reached 10.2 million followers.

She started taking it seriously while dating Josh Richards who was already successful on the platform.  They have since broken up following drama of Chase Hudson and her sharing a kiss.  All of the crisis in TikTok community has taken a toll on Nessa’s mental health and she has since opened up about it saying that she has been diagnosed with bipolar disorder.

She has just released her first single, “Pain”, and it has reached 4.9 million views within a week’s time.  Many believe this song is about ex-boyfriend Josh Richards.

songs.title: ​i hope ur miserable until ur dead
songs.title_with_featured: ​i hope ur miserable until ur dead

description.plain:
“i hope your miserable until your dead” is track 3 off of Nessa Barrett’s debut EP, Pretty Poison. As well as being the first single off of the EP.

The song was first teased on TikTok before being announced on Instagram on 27 July, 2021. The song was released on August 6, 2021, along with its music video.

The song is an pop rock anthem and is regarding someone who’s ruined her life and made her miserable and she’s hoping that they can feel the same pain she has felt.

As soon as the song was released last night, IHYMUYD started trending on Twitter. Nessa Barrett is even making her haters love her right now with her awesome music. The song I Hope You’re Miserable Until You’re Dead is released on her birthday today i.e. August 6, 2021. However, she celebrated her song release and birthday along with the surprise announcement of her EP dropping next month.

The song and the music video drop hints of her troubling relationship with her ex-boyfriend Josh Richards. Even though she did not explicitly called him out by name, many believe the lyrics are telling the whole story.

In her previously released song, Counting Crimes, Nessa shaded her ex-boyfriend by stating that her sins/crime are still less than him. In the new music video, Nessa Barrett is a ghost-girl haunting her ex-boyfriend for the things he did to her when she was “alive”.

So now Barrett is dumping him and “moving on”, even if internally she doesn’t really feel prepared to do so. And in response to being dumped, the addressee has gone about slandering her name. But alas, the vocalist too is “petty as fuck”. So instead of just going her way, she has decided to leave her own lasting impression upon his life.
